4jn.title: Lagrange theorem on subgroup size
4jn.clickbait: Lagrange's Theorem is an important restriction on the sizes of subgroups of a finite group.
4jn.text:
Lagrange's Theorem states that if $G$ is a finite [-3gd] and $H$ a subgroup, then the [-order] $|H|$ of $H$ divides the order $|G|$ of $G$.
It generalises to infinite groups: the statement then becomes that the [4j4 left cosets] form a [set_partition partition], and for any pair of cosets, there is a [499 bijection] between them.

# Proof

In full generality, the cosets [4j5 form a partition] and [4j8 are all in bijection].

To specialise this to the finite case, we have divided the $|G|$ elements of $G$ into buckets of size $|H|$ (namely, the cosets), so $|G|/|H|$ must in particular be an integer.
